ADDITIONAL TERMS (per AGPL Section 7):

Prohibition on Surveillance Capitalism:
This software may not be used by organizations whose primary business model
involves mass surveillance, data mining for behavioral prediction, or the sale
of user attention to advertisers without explicit, informed, opt-in consent
from each user.

Specifically prohibited uses include (but are not limited to):
- Deployment as part of advertising-funded services that profile users
- Integration with systems designed for mass behavioral surveillance
- Deployment in contexts that violate user privacy rights under GDPR, CCPA,
  or equivalent regulations

This restriction is enforceable under Section 7 of the AGPL v3 license.

